{"type":"message","id":"54e19c27","parentId":"e9762f10","timestamp":"2026-05-01T16:51:54.706Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Bobby is saying my messages are too long and he loses focus. He wants shorter, easier-to-digest replies. Let me acknowledge this and figure out what would help him.\n\nOptions:\n1. I just make my replies shorter and more bulleted\n2. Set up a system where I give him a quick summary first, then details if he wants them\n3. Numbered short answers\n4. Voice memos instead of long text\n5. A quick-reply system where I give him just the key decision point\n\nLet me ask him what would work best for him rather than assume.\n","thinkingSignature":"1fb3403aa2e92d781abcaa601ac58bbcee6e65bf4a88e025b8e42452c3a0bfd9"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nGood call — let's fix that now.\n\nA few options to make my replies shorter and easier to handle:\n\n1. **Bullets + numbers only** — I give you a quick numbered list, you pick, done\n2. **TL;DR first** — I put the one-line answer at the top, details below only if you want them\n3. **Voice memo** — I read it to you instead of wall-of-text\n4. **One thing at a time** — We tackle topics one by one instead of stacking everything in one message\n5. **Quick reactions** — You just react with a number or emoji and I handle the rest\n\nWhat works best for you? And is this a Telegram-only thing or are long replies a problem everywhere you chat with me?"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":77660,"output":281,"cacheRead":64,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":78005,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1777654300124,"responseId":"06440d1c64b6d4a3b4460c4c8e84bde4"}}
