{"type":"message","id":"085821f7","parentId":"5d4eff69","timestamp":"2026-05-01T19:19:07.909Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I need to write the server-side component. This is a Node.js server that:\n1. Receives the transcribed text from the HTML page\n2. Sends it to me (via some mechanism)\n3. Converts my response to audio using the `say` command\n4. Returns the audio file path to the HTML page\n\nFor the \"sending to Dean\" part - I need a way for the server to communicate with me. Options:\n1. Write to a file that I read periodically\n2. Use a webhook that I expose\n3. Write to a shared memory file\n4. Make it so the server itself talks to me via the OpenClaw gateway\n\nThe simplest approach that works locally: write a file with the message, and have the server poll for my response. But that's clunky.\n\n\nI think the cleanest solution is to have the server write messages to a file that I'll monitor, then I'll respond by writing back to another file where the server can pick it up. So the flow would be: HTML sends text to the server, server writes it to a file, I detect the new message and process it, write my response back, and then the server converts it to audio and returns it.\n\nFor this to work, I need a simple way to pass messages between the server and me. I'll set up two files in the Telephone directory—one for incoming messages from the server and one for my responses—and I'll poll for new messages periodically and write my responses as audio files back to the server.\n\nSetting up message passing files...\n","thinkingSignature":"acc206d4861c07d912d295635c4864d6893b5aa2810d095aa5a16f854e5bc8a4"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_pnz4gt0czd6t_1","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"const http = require('http');\nconst fs = require('fs');\nconst path = require('path');\nconst { execSync, exec } = require('child_process');\n\nconst PORT = 8791;\nconst DIR = __dirname;\n\nconst INBOX = path.join(DIR, 'inbox.txt');\nconst OUTBOX = path.join(DIR, 'outbox.txt');\nconst AUDIO_DIR = path.join(DIR, 'audio');\n\nif (!fs.existsSync(AUDIO_DIR)) fs.mkdirSync(AUDIO_DIR, { recursive: true });\nfs.writeFileSync(INBOX, '');\nfs.writeFileSync(OUTBOX, '');\n\nlet lastInbox = '';\nlet lastOutbox = '';\nlet pollingOutbox = false;\n\nfunction pollOutbox() {\n  if (pollingOutbox) return;\n  pollingOutbox = true;\n\n  const check = () => {\n    try {\n      const content = fs.readFileSync(OUTBOX, 'utf8').trim();\n      if (content && content !== lastOutbox) {\n        lastOutbox = content;\n        const timestamp = Date.now();\n        const mp3Path = path.join(AUDIO_DIR, `reply_${timestamp}.mp3`);\n\n        // Convert text to speech\n        execSync(`say \"${content.replace(/\"/g, '\\\\\"')}\" -o /tmp/dean_reply.aiff && ffmpeg -i /tmp/dean_reply.aiff \"${mp3Path}\" -y`, { stdio: 'pipe' });\n\n        // Clear outbox\n        fs.writeFileSync(OUTBOX, '');\n\n        // Send back to client\n        if (pendingResolve) {\n          pendingResolve({ audioFile: mp3Path });\n          pendingResolve = null;\n        }\n\n        // Also serve audio statically\n      }\n    } catch(e) {\n      console.error('Outbox poll error:', e.message);\n    }\n    setTimeout(check, 500);\n  };\n  check();\n}\n\nlet pendingResolve = null;\n\nconst server = http.createServer((req, res) => {\n  // CORS\n  res.setHeader('Access-Control-Allow-Origin', '*');\n  res.setHeader('Access-Control-Allow-Methods', 'GET, POST, OPTIONS');\n  res.setHeader('Access-Control-Allow-Headers', 'Content-Type');\n\n  if (req.method === 'OPTIONS') {\n    res.writeHead(200);\n    res.end();\n    return;\n  }\n\n  if (req.method === 'GET' && req.url.startsWith('/audio/')) {\n    const filename = path.basename(req.url);\n    const filePath = path.join(AUDIO_DIR, filename);\n    if (fs.existsSync(filePath)) {\n      res.writeHead(200, { 'Content-Type': 'audio/mpeg' });\n      fs.createReadStream(filePath).pipe(res);\n    } else {\n      res.writeHead(404);\n      res.end('Not found');\n    }\n    return;\n  }\n\n  if (req.method === 'POST' && req.url === '/talk') {\n    let body = '';\n    req.on('data', chunk => body += chunk);\n    req.on('end', () => {\n      try {\n        const { text } = JSON.parse(body);\n        fs.writeFileSync(INBOX, text);\n        lastInbox = text;\n\n        // Wait for audio response\n        const result = { audioFile: null };\n        const timeout = setTimeout(() => {\n          if (pendingResolve) {\n            pendingResolve({ audioFile: null });\n            pendingResolve = null;\n          }\n        }, 60000);\n\n        pendingResolve = (result) => {\n          clearTimeout(timeout);\n          res.writeHead(200, { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' });\n          res.end(JSON.stringify(result));\n        };\n\n        // Check if audio already available\n        const files = fs.readdirSync(AUDIO_DIR).sort().reverse();\n        for (const f of files) {\n          if (f.startsWith('reply_') && fs.statSync(path.join(AUDIO_DIR, f)).mtimeMs > Date.now() - 1000) {\n            if (pendingResolve) {\n              clearTimeout(timeout);\n              pendingResolve({ audioFile: `/talk/audio/${f}` });\n              pendingResolve = null;\n            }\n          }\n        }\n\n      } catch(e) {\n        res.writeHead(400);\n        res.end('Bad request');\n      }\n    });\n    return;\n  }\n\n  res.writeHead(404);\n  res.end('Not found');\n});\n\npollOutbox();\n\nserver.listen(PORT, () => {\n  console.log(`Telephone server running on port ${PORT}`);\n});","path":"/Users/bobbygalletta/Desktop/Telephone/server.js"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":2819,"output":1304,"cacheRead":82624,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":86747,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777663114443,"responseId":"06442f8a90efeb1cea28716ee2253d60"}}
