{"type":"message","id":"491bce82","parentId":"868825a4","timestamp":"2026-05-01T19:29:00.956Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The server.js is listening on port 8791 (IPv6), but port 8790 is not listening. The Python HTTP server that was serving port 8790 is no longer running. The telephone.html connects to port 8791 for the API and 8790 for serving the HTML page.\n\nWait - actually the telephone.html is served from port 8790 by the Python server. But the Python server is no longer running. Let me check if we can serve it from port 8791 instead, or restart the Python server on 8790.\n\nActually, looking at the server.js - it only handles /talk, /messages, /reply, and /audio/ routes. \n\nIt doesn't serve the HTML file itself. The telephone.html connects to `http://localhost:8791` for its API calls, so I need to either restart the Python server on 8790 to serve the static HTML file, or modify server.js to also serve static files.","thinkingSignature":"968e231d276b827c1480514d25745e33ffbc02f6ca4ce00fa87eac8e28fb14d5"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n\nServer.js and Dean are running on 8791, but the HTML file isn't being served anywhere. Let me fix that:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_1bd02407xcec_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"pkill -f \"http.server 8790\" 2>/dev/null; sleep 1 && cd ~/Desktop/Telephone && python3 -m http.server 8790 &\nsleep 1 && echo \"done\"","yieldMs":3000}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":112,"output":302,"cacheRead":97888,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":98302,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777663738103,"responseId":"064431faff008aefb76fdea8b8b4a3fa"}}
