{"type":"custom_message","customType":"openclaw.runtime-context","content":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"chat_id\": \"telegram:8212808444\",\n  \"message_id\": \"24091\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"8212808444\",\n  \"sender\": \"B G\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Fri 2026-05-01 15:30 EDT\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"B G (8212808444)\",\n  \"id\": \"8212808444\",\n  \"name\": \"B G\"\n}\n```","display":false,"details":{"source":"openclaw-runtime-context"},"id":"c7a92cd2","parentId":"2dd5ee65","timestamp":"2026-05-01T19:30:31.654Z"}
{"type":"message","id":"65160aec","parentId":"c7a92cd2","timestamp":"2026-05-01T19:31:11.145Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Bobby is saying Safari shows \"Speech not supported\" on the Telephone page. This means the Web Speech API isn't available or isn't working in Safari.\n\nThe Web Speech API requires HTTPS in most browsers for microphone access, or it needs specific permissions. Even on localhost, Safari might handle this differently.\n\nLet me think about solutions:\n1. Safari requires user permission for microphone access - needs a permissions prompt\n2. The Web Speech API might be disabled in Safari\n3. We might need to enable \"Allow Audio Input\" in Safari's settings\n\nActually, for the Web Speech API (`SpeechRecognition`), Safari has had support but it needs to be enabled and requires user permission for microphone access. The page probably isn't getting permission to use the microphone.\n \nThe issue is likely that the SpeechRecognition API isn't fully supported in Safari even though it exists—it requires explicit user permission for microphone access, which we haven't requested yet. A permissions prompt or manual enabling in Safari settings might be needed. I could switch to using the MediaRecorder API or MediaDevices API instead, which would handle microphone access more reliably, but that adds complexity since it requires a backend to handle the audio.\n\nLet me reconsider the approach here. For a local HTML file, the MediaDevices API should work if we request getUserMedia permission first, but the Web Speech API's recognition service might not initialize without a proper SSL context in Safari. I think the best path forward is to refactor the page to use getUserMedia for microphone capture, MediaRecorder to create an audio blob, and then send that to the server for transcription instead of relying on the browser's built-in speech recognition.\n","thinkingSignature":"63fbcb493f39fecbbc5ebe6f7d1fd9979471e6d2c04ffc84ff5c289b0e1720a6"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_qtberr3vidza_1","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n  <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\n  <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\">\n  <title>Telephone — Dean</title>\n  <style>\n    * { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }\n\n    body {\n      font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', sans-serif;\n      background: #0a0a0f;\n      color: #e0e0e0;\n      min-height: 100vh;\n      overflow: hidden;\n      user-select: none;\n    }\n\n    #fairy-canvas {\n      position: fixed;\n      top: 0; left: 0;\n      width: 100%; height: 100%;\n      z-index: 0;\n      pointer-events: none;\n    }\n\n    .ui {\n      position: relative;\n      z-index: 1;\n      display: flex;\n      flex-direction: column;\n      align-items: center;\n      justify-content: center;\n      min-height: 100vh;\n      gap: 24px;\n    }\n\n    .status {\n      font-size: 14px;\n      color: #666;\n      letter-spacing: 2px;\n      text-transform: uppercase;\n      min-height: 20px;\n    }\n\n    .status.listening { color: #ff6b6b; }\n    .status.thinking { color: #ffd93d; }\n    .status.replying { color: #6bffb8; }\n\n    .mic-btn {\n      width: 100px;\n      height: 100px;\n      border-radius: 50%;\n      border: 3px solid #333;\n      background: #1a1a24;\n      cursor: pointer;\n      display: flex;\n      align-items: center;\n      justify-content: center;\n      transition: all 0.2s;\n      position: relative;\n    }\n\n    .mic-btn:hover { border-color: #555; background: #222; }\n    .mic-btn.on { border-color: #ff6b6b; background: #2a1a1a; box-shadow: 0 0 30px rgba(255, 107, 107, 0.3); }\n\n    .mic-btn svg {\n      width: 36px;\n      height: 36px;\n      fill: #888;\n      transition: fill 0.2s;\n    }\n\n    .mic-btn.on svg { fill: #ff6b6b; }\n\n    .pulse-ring {\n      position: absolute;\n      width: 100%;\n      height: 100%;\n      border-radius: 50%;\n      border: 2px solid #ff6b6b;\n      opacity: 0;\n      animation: none;\n    }\n\n    .mic-btn.on .pulse-ring { animation: pulse 1.5s ease-out infinite; }\n\n    @keyframes pulse {\n      0% { transform: scale(1); opacity: 0.8; }\n      100% { transform: scale(1.8); opacity: 0; }\n    }\n\n    .transcript {\n      font-size: 13px;\n      color: #555;\n      max-width: 400px;\n      text-align: center;\n      min-height: 40px;\n      padding: 0 20px;\n    }\n\n    .transcript.visible { color: #aaa; }\n\n    .hint {\n      font-size: 12px;\n      color: #444;\n      position: fixed;\n      bottom: 30px;\n    }\n\n    .reply-indicator {\n      font-size: 12px;\n      color: #3a3a3a;\n      position: fixed;\n      bottom: 50px;\n      opacity: 0;\n      transition: opacity 0.3s;\n    }\n\n    .reply-indicator.show { opacity: 1; color: #6bffb8; }\n\n    .error-msg {\n      font-size: 13px;\n      color: #ff6b6b;\n      max-width: 300px;\n      text-align: center;\n      padding: 0 20px;\n    }\n  </style>\n</head>\n<body>\n\n<canvas id=\"fairy-canvas\"></canvas>\n\n<div class=\"ui\">\n  <div class=\"status\" id=\"status\">Tap to talk</div>\n  <button class=\"mic-btn\" id=\"mic-btn\">\n    <div class=\"pulse-ring\"></div>\n    <svg viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"><path d=\"M12 14c1.66 0 3-1.34 3-3V5c0-1.66-1.34-3-3-3S9 3.34 9 5v6c0 1.66 1.34 3 3 3zm5.91-3c-.49 0-.9.36-.98.85C16.52 14.2 14.47 16 12 16s-4.52-1.8-4.93-4.15c-.08-.49-.49-.85-.98-.85-.61 0-1.09.54-1 1.14.49 3 2.89 5.35 5.91 5.78V20c0 .55.45 1 1 1s1-.45 1-1v-2.08c3.02-.43 5.42-2.78 5.91-5.78.1-.6-.39-1.14-1-1.14z\"/></svg>\n  </button>\n  <div class=\"transcript\" id=\"transcript\"></div>\n  <div class=\"error-msg\" id=\"error-msg\"></div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"reply-indicator\" id=\"reply-indicator\">Dean is replying...</div>\n<div class=\"hint\">Tap mic to talk — Dean replies with voice</div>\n\n<script>\n// === Fairy Light System ===\nconst canvas = document.getElementById('fairy-canvas');\nconst ctx = canvas.getContext('2d');\nlet lights = [];\nlet currentMode = 'idle';\n\nfunction resizeCanvas() {\n  canvas.width = window.innerWidth;\n  canvas.height = window.innerHeight;\n}\nresizeCanvas();\nwindow.addEventListener('resize', resizeCanvas);\n\nconst NUM_LIGHTS = 60;\nfor (let i = 0; i < NUM_LIGHTS; i++) {\n  lights.push({\n    x: Math.random() * canvas.width,\n    y: Math.random() * canvas.height,\n    vx: (Math.random() - 0.5) * 0.5,\n    vy: (Math.random() - 0.5) * 0.5,\n    size: Math.random() * 3 + 1,\n    brightness: Math.random() * 0.5 + 0.3,\n    hue: Math.random() * 60 + 20,\n    twinkle: Math.random() * Math.PI * 2,\n    twinkleSpeed: Math.random() * 0.05 + 0.02\n  });\n}\n\nfunction drawLight(l, intensity) {\n  const alpha = l.brightness * intensity;\n  ctx.save();\n  ctx.globalAlpha = alpha;\n  ctx.fillStyle = `hsl(${l.hue}, 80%, 70%)`;\n  ctx.shadowBlur = 15 * intensity;\n  ctx.shadowColor = `hsl(${l.hue}, 90%, 60%)`;\n  ctx.beginPath();\n  ctx.arc(l.x, l.y, l.size * (0.8 + intensity * 0.4), 0, Math.PI * 2);\n  ctx.fill();\n  ctx.restore();\n}\n\nfunction updateLights() {\n  for (let l of lights) {\n    l.x += l.vx;\n    l.y += l.vy;\n    l.twinkle += l.twinkleSpeed;\n    if (l.x < 0 || l.x > canvas.width) l.vx *= -1;\n    if (l.y < 0 || l.y > canvas.height) l.vy *= -1;\n    l.vx += (Math.random() - 0.5) * 0.02;\n    l.vy += (Math.random() - 0.5) * 0.02;\n    l.vx = Math.max(-1, Math.min(1, l.vx));\n    l.vy = Math.max(-1, Math.min(1, l.vy));\n  }\n}\n\nfunction getIntensity() {\n  if (currentMode === 'listening') return 1.8;\n  if (currentMode === 'replying') return 2.0;\n  if (currentMode === 'thinking') return 0.4 + Math.sin(Date.now() * 0.005) * 0.4;\n  return 0.8 + Math.sin(Date.now() * 0.001) * 0.15;\n}\n\nfunction animate() {\n  ctx.clearRect(0, 0, canvas.width, canvas.height);\n  updateLights();\n  const intensity = getIntensity();\n  for (let l of lights) {\n    const tw = 0.7 + Math.sin(l.twinkle) * 0.3;\n    drawLight(l, intensity * tw);\n  }\n  requestAnimationFrame(animate);\n}\nanimate();\n\n// === Audio Recording & Transcription ===\nconst micBtn = document.getElementById('mic-btn');\nconst status = document.getElementById('status');\nconst transcript = document.getElementById('transcript');\nconst replyIndicator = document.getElementById('reply-indicator');\nconst errorMsg = document.getElementById('error-msg');\n\nlet mediaRecorder = null;\nlet audioChunks = [];\nlet isRecording = false;\nlet audioStream = null;\nlet recognition = null;\nlet finalTranscript = '';\n\n// Try Web Speech API first\nif ('webkitSpeechRecognition' in window || 'SpeechRecognition' in window) {\n  const SR = window.SpeechRecognition || window.webkitSpeechRecognition;\n  recognition = new SR();\n  recognition.continuous = true;\n  recognition.interimResults = true;\n  recognition.lang = 'en-US';\n\n  recognition.onresult = (event) => {\n    let interim = '';\n    for (let i = event.resultIndex; i < event.results.length; i++) {\n      if (event.results[i].isFinal) {\n        finalTranscript = event.results[i][0].transcript.trim();\n      } else {\n        interim += event.results[i][0].transcript;\n      }\n    }\n    transcript.textContent = interim || finalTranscript;\n    if (interim || finalTranscript) transcript.classList.add('visible');\n  };\n\n  recognition.onerror = (e) => {\n    console.error('SR error:', e);\n    if (e.error === 'not-allowed') {\n      showError('Microphone access denied. Allow mic in Safari settings.');\n    }\n  };\n\n  recognition.onend = () => {\n    if (isRecording && recognition) {\n      try { recognition.start(); } catch(e) {}\n    }\n  };\n}\n\nfunction showError(msg) {\n  errorMsg.textContent = msg;\n}\n\nasync function startListening() {\n  errorMsg.textContent = '';\n  finalTranscript = '';\n  transcript.textContent = '';\n  transcript.classList.remove('visible');\n\n  // Use MediaRecorder approach for audio capture\n  try {\n    audioStream = await navigator.mediaDevices.getUserMedia({ audio: true });\n  } catch(e) {\n    showError('Microphone access denied. Check Safari permissions.');\n    return;\n  }\n\n  isRecording = true;\n  currentMode = 'listening';\n  micBtn.classList.add('on');\n  status.textContent = 'Listening...';\n  status.className = 'status listening';\n\n  audioChunks = [];\n\n  // Use MediaRecorder to capture audio\n  const mimeType = MediaRecorder.isTypeSupported('audio/webm') ? 'audio/webm' : 'audio/mp4';\n  mediaRecorder = new MediaRecorder(audioStream, { mimeType });\n\n  mediaRecorder.ondataavailable = (event) => {\n    if (event.data.size > 0) audioChunks.push(event.data);\n  };\n\n  mediaRecorder.onstop = async () => {\n    if (audioChunks.length > 0 && finalTranscript.trim()) {\n      sendText(finalTranscript.trim());\n    }\n    audioChunks = [];\n  };\n\n  mediaRecorder.start();\n\n  // Also start speech recognition if available\n  if (recognition) {\n    try { recognition.start(); } catch(e) {}\n  }\n}\n\nfunction stopListening() {\n  if (!isRecording) return;\n  isRecording = false;\n\n  if (recognition) {\n    try { recognition.stop(); } catch(e) {}\n  }\n\n  if (mediaRecorder && mediaRecorder.state !== 'inactive') {\n    mediaRecorder.stop();\n  }\n\n  if (audioStream) {\n    audioStream.getTracks().forEach(t => t.stop());\n  }\n\n  micBtn.classList.remove('on');\n\n  if (finalTranscript.trim()) {\n    sendText(finalTranscript.trim());\n  }\n\n  finalTranscript = '';\n}\n\nmicBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {\n  if (isRecording) {\n    stopListening();\n  } else {\n    startListening();\n  }\n});\n\nasync function sendText(text) {\n  status.textContent = 'Waiting for Dean...';\n  status.className = 'status';\n  currentMode = 'idle';\n\n  try {\n    await fetch('http://localhost:8791/talk', {\n      method: 'POST',\n      headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },\n      body: JSON.stringify({ text })\n    });\n\n    pollForReply();\n  } catch(e) {\n    status.textContent = 'Error — tap to retry';\n    currentMode = 'idle';\n  }\n}\n\nlet lastReplyCheck = 0;\n\nasync function pollForReply() {\n  const checkReply = async () => {\n    try {\n      const resp = await fetch('http://localhost:8791/messages?since=' + lastReplyCheck);\n      const data = await resp.json();\n\n      const deanMsg = data.messages?.find(m => m.from === 'dean');\n      if (deanMsg && deanMsg.audioFile) {\n        lastReplyCheck = deanMsg.timestamp;\n        currentMode = 'replying';\n        status.textContent = 'Dean';\n        status.className = 'status replying';\n        replyIndicator.classList.add('show');\n\n        const audio = new Audio('http://localhost:8791' + deanMsg.audioFile);\n        audio.play();\n\n        audio.onended = () => {\n          currentMode = 'idle';\n          status.textContent = 'Tap to talk';\n          status.className = 'status';\n          replyIndicator.classList.remove('show');\n        };\n\n        audio.onerror = () => {\n          currentMode = 'idle';\n          status.textContent = 'Tap to talk';\n          status.className = 'status';\n          replyIndicator.classList.remove('show');\n        };\n\n        return;\n      }\n\n      if (currentMode !== 'replying') {\n        status.textContent = 'Dean is thinking...';\n        status.className = 'status thinking';\n        currentMode = 'thinking';\n      }\n\n      setTimeout(checkReply, 2000);\n\n    } catch(e) {\n      setTimeout(checkReply, 3000);\n    }\n  };\n\n  checkReply();\n}\n</script>\n</body>\n</html>","path":"/Users/bobbygalletta/Desktop/Telephone/telephone.html"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":98067,"output":3628,"cacheRead":128,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":101823,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777663831654,"responseId":"064432587e3fd9534b4e0aa635039232"}}
